text: Wazner is an european family name, also Wazenez or Wadjenedj, was a Predynastic Egyptian king who ruled in the Nile Delta.J. H. Breasted, History of Egypt from the Earliest Time to the Persian Conquest, 1909, p.36Harold Peake, Herbert John Fleure, Priests and Kings, Kessinger Publishing 2003, p.63 He is mentioned in the Palermo Stone inscriptions among a small number of kings of Lower Egypt.J.
